.TH "RTCINBOUNDRTPSTREAMSTATS.PACKETSDISCARDED" "3JS" "August 15, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
RTCInboundRtpStreamStats.packetsDiscarded \- RTCInboundRtpStreamStats:
packetsDiscarded property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]packetsDiscarded\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]RTCInboundRtpStreamStats\f[R] dictionary indicates the cumulative
number of RTP packets that have been discarded by the jitter buffer due
to late or early\-arrival, and are hence not played out.
.PP
The value does not include packets that are discarded to due to packet
duplication.
.SH VALUE
An positive integer value.
.PP
This is calculated as defined in RFC 7002, section 3.2 (and appendix
A.a.)
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]packetsLost\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]packetsReceived\f[R]
